&lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/work/terms/refocusing/>
  rdf:type schema:Article ;
  schema:url &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/work/terms/refocusing/> ;
  schema:name "Refocusing" ;
  schema:description "A Refocusing is a morphism (H, t*) → (H', t') between MacroFoci — a pair (ρ, φ) of a presheaf transition ρ and a history reassignment φ that moves the designated focal history from t* to t'. Three structurally distinct cases: forward extension (t' = s★t*, H' = G_s(H)), backward restriction (t' \u003c t*, H' = H), and lateral shift (t' incomparable with t*, H' = H). In every case the new MacroFocus (H', t') is fully constituted by the refocusing; the Gurwitsch tripartition reconstitutes around t'. Formally a morphism in the category of pointed presheaves." ;
  schema:datePublished "2026-03-20" ;
  schema:dateModified "2026-03-20" ;
  schema:about &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/work/terms/refocusing/> ;
  rdfs:seeAlso "MacroFocus, Focus, MesoFocus, RelationalMachine, RelationalState, Passage" ;
  schema:identifier &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/work/terms/refocusing/> .

